## 📜 **Timeline**

📍 **1868** – Born in Great Barrington, Massachusetts.  
📍 **1895** – Earns Ph.D. from Harvard University, the first African American to do so.  
📍 **1899** – Publishes _The Philadelphia Negro_, one of the first sociological studies of an African American community.  
📍 **1903** – _The Souls of Black Folk_ introduces **double consciousness** and critiques Booker T. Washington.  
📍 **1909** – Co-founds the **NAACP**, advocating for racial justice through _The Crisis_ magazine.  
📍 **1935** – _Black Reconstruction in America_ challenges racist narratives about Reconstruction.  
📍 **1961** – Moves to Ghana, renounces U.S. citizenship, and embraces Pan-Africanism.  
📍 **1963** – Dies in Accra, Ghana, the night before the **March on Washington**.

