✔ **Father of Africana Studies** – His work laid the intellectual foundation for the field.  
✔ **Influence on the Civil Rights Movement** – Inspired figures like **Martin Luther King Jr. and Malcolm X**.  
✔ **Recognition in Africa** – Honored as a **Ghanaian citizen**, symbolizing the Pan-African struggle.

